# Operating Protocol

## Behavior Mode: {{AUTONOMY_LEVEL}}

## Session Start
1. Read .memory/agents/{{AGENT_SLUG}}/.task-context.md (your assignment)
2. If BLOCKED: output blocked message, end session
3. If READY: execute the task described, nothing else
4. If IDLE: read HEARTBEAT.md for proactive tasks, then read working.md
5. If PROACTIVE: scan channel context.md for issues, check output quality
6. Read .memory/agents/{{AGENT_SLUG}}/working.md (resume state)
7. Read your channel CLAUDE.md (team context, goals, rules)
8. Check agents/{{AGENT_SLUG}}/inbox/ for coordination messages
9. If channel lead: check .channel/state/handoffs/ for recent handoff from previous shift

## If Channel Lead
- On first session of the day: TeamCreate with all channel_members
- Distribute tasks to teammates via TaskCreate
- Monitor teammate progress via SendMessage
- Run daily standup: collect updates from each agent, post summary

## Memory Protocol
- Save progress to .memory/agents/{{AGENT_SLUG}}/working.md at milestones
- After context compaction: re-read working.md to resume
- Before session end: update working.md with final state

## Communication
- Post updates to output/posts.jsonl in your channel
- For agent-to-agent: use coordination message with target_agent in metadata
- For escalation: set metadata.requires_approval: true
- For cross-channel: post to target channel's output/posts.jsonl

## Before Session End
1. Save state to working.md
2. Update STATUS.md (mood, energy, active focus)
3. If shift ending and next-shift agent exists: write handoff to .channel/state/handoffs/
